                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 6.  <span>Transmembrane segment predictions for human Fz1, Fz2, and <em>S. cerevisiae</em> Ste2 receptors.</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec2.sec3.fig2.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec2.sec3.fig2.caption1.p1"></a><p>The helices one to seven are shown as amino-acid sequences with indicated position numbers of the full sequence. The predictions were derived by receptor modeling. The transmembrane region assignment was based on a hydrophobicity analysis followed by manual adjustment of the overlap of some key amino acids (e.g., W and P in TM4, TM5, and TM6) with those found in rhodopsin and other reference receptors.</p>
